My former implementation need buf as global variable, but now we don't have to keep it global, so I converted it into local.
Also I fixed misusing of codec in `NettyChannelInitializer` and sync in `NettyHttpLink`.
@taegeonum Thank you for your review!

@motus @markusweimer 

By the way,  I want to bring up that this unit test seems never to be tested for Windows in the integration build. As far as I checked, we only have Java Build running on Linux, and .NET build running on Windows - https://github.com/apache/reef

There is no Java Build in Windows.  I found this failure when I have this code run on Windows.

@homezcx Oh, so maybe it had never worked  (Just kidding)
But seriously, maybe we should use some more reliable way to get the PID?
BTW, Unix version also looks suspicious - e.g. we cannot expect `bash` to be present on every system (although it is usually there)
